    },
    {
      "type": "rectangle",
      "id": "el-116",
      "x": 8560,
      "y": 580,
      "width": 1760,
      "height": 120,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "#fff4e6",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "strokeWidth": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "el-117",
      "x": 8600,
      "y": 600,
      "width": 588.0,
      "height": 32,
      "text": "The AI Agent IS the Template Engine",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "el-118",
      "x": 8600,
      "y": 645,
      "width": 1017.5999999999999,
      "height": 60,
      "text": "No Jinja2. No Ansible. No hand-written Python.\nIt reads structured data from Nautobot, understands protocol semantics, and generates vendor-specific CLI.\nChange the data model \u2192 the config follows automatically.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#495057"
    },
    {
      "type": "rectangle",
      "id": "el-119",
      "x": 8560,
      "y": 750,
      "width": 1760,
      "height": 200,
      "strokeColor": "#495057",
      "backgroundColor": "#f8f9fa",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "strokeWidth": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "el-120",
      "x": 8600,
      "y": 770,
      "width": 528.0,
      "height": 26,
      "text": "For Advanced Viewers \u2014 Design Principles",
      "fontSize": 22,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#495057"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "el-121",
      "x": 8600,
      "y": 810,
      "width": 837.0,
      "height": 95,
      "text": "\u2460 Data-driven, not template-driven \u2014 derive config from data model semantics\n\u2461 Protocol-aware ordering \u2014 push sequence respects convergence dependencies (OSPF before BGP)\n\u2462 Idempotent intent \u2014 re-run produces same result; FRR merges additive config\n\u2463 SOT-first, always \u2014 never hardcode device facts; always query the source of truth\n\u2464 Validate, don't trust \u2014 match expected state against actual state after every change",
      "fontSize": 15,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#495057"
    },
    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "el-122",
      "x": 10600,
      "y": 0,
      "width": 1920,
      "height": 1080,
      "name": "Scene 6 \u2014 Protocol Participation",
      "strokeColor": "#495057",
      "strokeWidth": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "el-123",
      "x": 10700,
      "y": 60,
      "width": 720.0,
      "height": 52,
      "text": "NetClaw Joins the Network",
      "fontSize": 48,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "el-124",
      "x": 10700,
      "y": 120,
      "width": 624.0,
      "height": 24,
      "text": "From operator to participant \u2014 the agent IS a router",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#868e96"
    },
    {
      "type": "rectangle",
